Parkinson's Law: Work expands so as to fill the time available for its completion. - Cyril Northcote Parkinson, British civil servant, first published in 'The Economist' (1955)
%
Parkinson's Law - Stock-Sanford Corollary: If you wait until the last minute, it only takes a minute to do.
%
Parkinson's Law - Data Corollary: Data expands to fill the space available for storage.
%
Generalized form of Parkinson's Law: The demand upon a resource tends to expand to match the supply of the resource. The reverse is not true.
%
